161    /**
162    * Iterate through the nodes, collect all the NAME nodes that need to be
163    * renamed, and count how many times each variable name is referenced.
164    *
165    * There are 2 passes:
166    * - externs: keep track of the global vars in the externNames_ map.
167    * - source: keep track of all name references in globalNameNodes_, and
168    * localNameNodes_.
169    *
170    * To get shorter local variable renaming, we rename local variables to a
171    * temporary name "LOCAL_VAR_PREFIX + index" where index is the index of the
172    * variable declared in the local scope stack.
173    * e.g.
174    * Foo(fa, fb) {
175    * var c = function(d, e) { return fa; }
176    * }
177    * The indexes are: fa:0, fb:1, c:2, d:3, e:4
178    *
179    * In that way, local variable names are reused in each global function.
180    * e.g. the final code might look like
181    * function x(a,b) { ... }
182    * function y(a,b,c) { ... }
183    */
